
[1]sightly

   SIGHTLY, a.

   1. Pleasing to the eye; striking to the view.

   Many brave sightly horses. We have thirty members, the most sightly of
                         all her majesty's subjects.

   2. Open to the view; that may be seen from a distance. We say; a house
   stands in a sightly place.
